## 12. SLA SYSTEM (3-LEVEL)

Default: 30 min. Saved with hotel_id. onConflict: 'department,hotel_id'
fetchSLA runs on MOUNT and EVERY POLL CYCLE → picks up manager changes live

Level 1 (80%): Orange warning
Level 2 (100%): Red + marks Violated in DB + mandatory delay reason
Level 3 (150%): Escalation notification

getSLALimit: slaSettings[dept] || 30 — consistent everywhere
handleComplete: blocks if elapsed > limit || task.status === 'Violated'

---

## 13. HOUSEKEEPING SYSTEM

Statuses: Clean | Dirty | Cleaning | Inspected | Do Not Disturb | Out of Order | Checked Out

INSPECTED ACCESS:
- HK Attendant → CANNOT select (filtered out in StaffPortal)
- HK Supervisor → CAN select (occupation === 'Housekeeping Supervisor' check)
- HK Manager → CAN (DeptManagerDashboard has all statuses)

CHECKED OUT FLOW:
1. Room status → Checked Out
2. guests table row deleted by room_number (no hotel_id column in guests)
3. Room fields cleared: assigned_to, cleaning_at, cleaned_at, inspected_at = null
4. Realtime DELETE event fires on guest's checkoutChannel → instant logout
5. Guest cannot re-login without QR scan (guests record gone)

